WEBVTT

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:06.960
<v Teacher>So what was is or he is, she is, it is?

00:00:06.960 --> 00:00:07.760
<v Student>S.

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:08.560
<v Teacher>S.

00:00:08.620 --> 00:00:09.340
<v Teacher>Good.

00:00:09.340 --> 00:00:14.940
<v Teacher>We can use this with some other convertible words as well to make sentences.

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:22.300
<v Teacher>Another rule for for these convertible words is that words in English the end A N T

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:29.640
<v Teacher>or ENT, most of them we can just stick an E on the end and they become Spanish.

00:00:29.640 --> 00:00:31.000
<v Teacher>So for example

00:00:31.640 --> 00:00:36.040
<v Teacher>Important becomes importante.

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:37.400
<v Teacher>Importante.

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.560
<v Teacher>Where is the stress there?

00:00:40.620 --> 00:00:43.340
<v Student>In the second last good.

00:00:43.340 --> 00:00:49.580
<v Teacher>The stress is as much part of the word as the sounds, which is why we want to get

00:00:49.740 --> 00:00:59.820
<v Teacher>into the habit of just processing where is the accent, not trying to memorize it, just looking where it is, not trying to memorize it, just observing it.

00:00:59.820 --> 00:01:02.940
<v Teacher>So how would you say it is important?

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:06.620
<v Teacher>Es importante.

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:09.100
<v Teacher>It's not important.

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:10.780
<v Student>No es importante.

00:01:10.780 --> 00:01:12.140
<v Teacher>No es importante.

00:01:12.140 --> 00:01:13.980
<v Teacher>How do you say different?

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:15.760
<v Student>Differente?

00:01:15.760 --> 00:01:16.640
<v Teacher>Differente.

00:01:16.640 --> 00:01:19.040
<v Teacher>It's not different.

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:20.560
<v Student>No es different.

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:21.120
<v Teacher>Good.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:23.600
<v Teacher>No es diferente.

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:26.240
<v Teacher>How would you say constant?

00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:27.040
<v Teacher>Constant

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:29.660
<v Student>Constante?

00:01:29.660 --> 00:01:31.500
<v Teacher>Yeah, constante.

00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:34.700
<v Teacher>How would you say it is constant?

00:01:34.700 --> 00:01:36.700
<v Student>Es constante.

00:01:36.700 --> 00:01:38.380
<v Teacher>Es constante.

00:01:38.540 --> 00:01:45.500
<v Teacher>If you add on mente, mente, this sound, you get li in English.

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:47.740
<v Teacher>If you want to say constant li

00:01:48.360 --> 00:01:51.880
<v Teacher>You can say constantemente.

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:53.240
<v Teacher>And it's one word.

00:01:53.240 --> 00:01:55.159
<v Teacher>Constantemente.

00:01:55.479 --> 00:01:57.159
<v Student>Constantemente.

00:01:57.159 --> 00:01:57.960
<v Student>Good.

00:01:57.960 --> 00:02:00.759
<v Teacher>So how would you say legally?

00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:04.400
<v Student>Legal legalmente.

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:05.200
<v Teacher>Perfect.

00:02:05.200 --> 00:02:06.320
<v Teacher>Legalmente.

00:02:06.320 --> 00:02:07.040
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:08.400
<v Teacher>Illegally?

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:09.680
<v Student>Illegalmente.

00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:11.760
<v Teacher>Illegalmente.

00:02:11.820 --> 00:02:15.900
<v Teacher>How do you think you say real in Spanish real?

00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:17.900
<v Teacher>Real Real good.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:23.180
<v Teacher>When we have an R at the beginning you might hear it like a rolling R real.

00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.820
<v Teacher>How do you think you would say really?

00:02:26.240 --> 00:02:27.440
<v Student>Realmente.

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:28.720
<v Teacher>Realmente.

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:35.840
<v Teacher>Real also means royal, like Real Madrid is not, you know, Real Madrid, it's Royal Madrid.

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:38.400
<v Teacher>How do you say normally?

00:02:39.460 --> 00:02:40.660
<v Student>Normalmente.

00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:41.300
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:42.820
<v Teacher>Normalmente.

00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:47.540
<v Teacher>So what would it mean if I said to you

00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:51.040
<v Teacher>Normalmente es importante.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:53.920
<v Teacher>Normalmente es importante.

00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:55.840
<v Teacher>What does that mean?

00:02:55.720 --> 00:02:59.560
<v Student>Well n normally as in usually it's important it's important.

00:02:59.560 --> 00:03:00.200
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:00.920
<v Teacher>This is true.

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:03.959
<v Teacher>You actually use normally like uh usually.

00:03:03.959 --> 00:03:06.760
<v Teacher>Normalmente es importante.

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:21.660
<v Teacher>Now if we have the j sound, a j sound in a convertible word, so we're not working with the letter G, we are working with the sound here, we're thinking about the sound.

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:27.240
<v Teacher>If we have a ju sound in a convertible word, this j is going to become h in Spanish.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:35.880
<v Teacher>Now, if you know how to say Argentina, for example, in Spanish, Argentina, if you've heard that anywhere, this is a good hook to remember this rule.

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.940
<v Teacher>If we have a just sound, it's gonna become ch as a sound.

00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:41.540
<v Teacher>So this doesn't mean any g.

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:43.860
<v Teacher>For example, how would you say global?

00:03:43.860 --> 00:03:44.580
<v Student>Global.

00:03:44.739 --> 00:03:45.620
<v Teacher>Global.

00:03:45.620 --> 00:03:47.060
<v Teacher>Globally.

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:48.240
<v Student>Globalmente.

00:03:48.240 --> 00:03:48.880
<v Teacher>Globalmente.

00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:52.240
<v Teacher>So it's not a G, it's the G sound.

00:03:52.240 --> 00:03:55.600
<v Teacher>General is gonna become General.

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:56.160
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:03:56.160 --> 00:03:56.800
<v Teacher>General.

00:03:56.800 --> 00:04:00.160
<v Teacher>So we're causing a bit of friction in the float general.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:00.960
<v Teacher>Generally

00:04:01.599 --> 00:04:02.800
<v Student>Generalmente.

00:04:02.800 --> 00:04:03.920
<v Teacher>Generalmente.

00:04:03.920 --> 00:04:04.720
<v Teacher>Good.

00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:06.640
<v Teacher>Original.

00:04:06.959 --> 00:04:07.920
<v Teacher>Original.

00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:08.959
<v Teacher>Original.

00:04:08.959 --> 00:04:10.319
<v Teacher>Originally.

00:04:11.020 --> 00:04:12.380
<v Student>Originalmente.

00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:12.780
<v Teacher>Good.

00:04:12.780 --> 00:04:14.380
<v Teacher>Originalmente.

00:04:14.380 --> 00:04:16.299
<v Teacher>Digital?

00:04:16.299 --> 00:04:17.260
<v Teacher>Digital.

00:04:17.260 --> 00:04:18.140
<v Teacher>Digital.

00:04:18.140 --> 00:04:18.940
<v Teacher>Good.

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:20.700
<v Teacher>Naturally.

00:04:21.060 --> 00:04:22.420
<v Student>Naturalmente.

00:04:22.420 --> 00:04:22.820
<v Teacher>Good.

00:04:22.820 --> 00:04:26.500
<v Teacher>How would you say naturally it's original?

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:29.540
<v Student>Naturalmente es original.

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:29.940
<v Student>Good.

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:34.820
<v Teacher>So naturalente you can also use it a little bit like obviously, something like that.

00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:42.680
<v Teacher>Words ending IBLE or ABLE, we can also convert many of them.

00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:46.440
<v Teacher>We just have to pronounce it syllable by syllable and put the accent

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:47.860
<v Teacher>Second from the end.

00:04:47.860 --> 00:04:51.460
<v Teacher>So possible becomes possible.

00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:52.580
<v Student>Possible.

00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:54.420
<v Teacher>Probable?

00:04:54.420 --> 00:04:55.380
<v Student>Probable?

00:04:55.380 --> 00:04:55.860
<v Student>Yeah.

00:04:55.860 --> 00:04:56.580
<v Teacher>Probably.

00:04:56.580 --> 00:04:58.740
<v Teacher>How do you say probable?

00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:00.760
<v Student>Probablemente.

00:05:00.760 --> 00:05:01.320
<v Teacher>Yeah.

00:05:01.320 --> 00:05:02.680
<v Teacher>Probablemente.

00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:04.680
<v Teacher>Possibly.

00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:06.520
<v Student>Possiblemente.

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:07.160
<v Student>Good.

00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:07.800
<v Teacher>Possibly.

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:09.480
<v Teacher>It's original.

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:12.780
<v Student>Possiblemente es original.

00:05:12.780 --> 00:05:13.260
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:13.260 --> 00:05:16.220
<v Teacher>Possiblemente es original.

00:05:16.220 --> 00:05:17.900
<v Teacher>Flexible?

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:19.560
<v Student>Flexible.

00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:20.520
<v Teacher>Flexible.

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:20.919
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:20.919 --> 00:05:24.360
<v Teacher>So you can't do this like if you say doable, for example.

00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:29.879
<v Teacher>You know, it's when the able or ibble is really part of the word, you will probably be able to do this.

00:05:29.360 --> 00:05:35.200
<v Teacher>Some of these rules are more useful than others, some of these rules have more exceptions than others.

00:05:35.200 --> 00:05:39.840
<v Teacher>We want to just get in the habit of identifying them and then getting this sense of

00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:45.800
<v Teacher>what words in English are from Latin and which ones we can experiment with converting over to Spanish.

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:51.720
<v Teacher>Now this gives us over 3,000 words and they are enough words to be very conversational.

00:05:51.639 --> 00:06:01.800
<v Teacher>So we want to feel free to experiment with the vocabulary, but at the same time we don't want to feel restricted by the fact that we might find an exception or we might use one that doesn't work

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:07.520
<v Teacher>And feeling comfortable about that possibility of making that error is what really allows you to learn quickly.

00:06:07.520 --> 00:06:13.200
<v Teacher>Because with this experimentation, you find very quickly the words that you can use

